<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="144" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,327,2017]" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,327,352]" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[449,518,327,352]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1931,1954]" captionTargetBox="[168,1408,290,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,280,1905]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Polana (Angusana) pilosa sp. nov., male holotype. 1, head, frontal view. 2, forewing. 3, sternite VIII, ventral view. 4, pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view. 5, subgenital plate, ventral view. 6, connective and styles, dorsal view. 7, style, lateral view. 8, aedeagus, lateral view. 9, aedeagus, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457643/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, narrowed on apical half; style (
<figureCitation box="[1066,1167,327,352]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1931,1954]" captionTargetBox="[168,1408,290,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,280,1905]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Polana (Angusana) pilosa sp. nov., male holotype. 1, head, frontal view. 2, forewing. 3, sternite VIII, ventral view. 4, pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view. 5, subgenital plate, ventral view. 6, connective and styles, dorsal view. 7, style, lateral view. 8, aedeagus, lateral view. 9, aedeagus, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457643/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Figs 6, 7</figureCitation>
) with apex bearing tiny dorsal denticles; aedeagal shaft (
<figureCitation box="[536,646,364,389]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1931,1954]" captionTargetBox="[168,1408,290,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,280,1905]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Polana (Angusana) pilosa sp. nov., male holotype. 1, head, frontal view. 2, forewing. 3, sternite VIII, ventral view. 4, pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view. 5, subgenital plate, ventral view. 6, connective and styles, dorsal view. 7, style, lateral view. 8, aedeagus, lateral view. 9, aedeagus, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457643/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Figs 8, 9</figureCitation>
) with pair of small apical processes; processes of dorsal apodeme bilobate at apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="145" pageId="1" pageNumber="144" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,327,2017]" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,436,461]" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Description</emphasis>
(male 
<typeStatus box="[429,532,436,461]" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">holotype</typeStatus>
). Length 8.7 mm. Head (
<figureCitation box="[844,935,436,461]" captionStart="FIGURES 40–47" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1936,1959]" captionTargetBox="[166,1425,270,1812]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,243,1868]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 40–47. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively. 40 and 41, Polana (A.) pilosa sp. nov., male holotype. 42 and 43, P. (A.) exornata (Fowler, 1903), male allotype. 44 and 45, P. (D.) maculosa sp. nov., male holotype. 46 and 47, P. (D.) danesa DeLong &amp; Freytag, 1972, male holotype. Scale bar = 2.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457651/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, not produced anteriorly; distinctly narrower than pronotum; transocular width about three-fourths of humeral width of pronotum. Crown (
<figureCitation box="[159,247,508,533]" captionStart="FIGURES 40–47" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1936,1959]" captionTargetBox="[166,1425,270,1812]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,243,1868]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 40–47. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively. 40 and 41, Polana (A.) pilosa sp. nov., male holotype. 42 and 43, P. (A.) exornata (Fowler, 1903), male allotype. 44 and 45, P. (D.) maculosa sp. nov., male holotype. 46 and 47, P. (D.) danesa DeLong &amp; Freytag, 1972, male holotype. Scale bar = 2.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457651/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
) short, median length approximately two-fifths of interocular width; anterior and posterior margins approximately parallel, anterior margin slightly rounded; surface slightly concave; texture with parallel transverse striations; coronal suture distinct on basal half of crown. Ocellus large; equidistant between anterior and posterior margins of crown; closer to midline than to adjacent compound eye. Transition between crown and face (
<figureCitation box="[1346,1428,615,640]" captionStart="FIGURES 40–47" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1936,1959]" captionTargetBox="[166,1425,270,1812]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,243,1868]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 40–47. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively. 40 and 41, Polana (A.) pilosa sp. nov., male holotype. 42 and 43, P. (A.) exornata (Fowler, 1903), male allotype. 44 and 45, P. (D.) maculosa sp. nov., male holotype. 46 and 47, P. (D.) danesa DeLong &amp; Freytag, 1972, male holotype. Scale bar = 2.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457651/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Fig. 41</figureCitation>
) defined, broad; transversely striated. Face (
<figureCitation box="[635,699,652,677]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1931,1954]" captionTargetBox="[168,1408,290,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,280,1905]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Polana (Angusana) pilosa sp. nov., male holotype. 1, head, frontal view. 2, forewing. 3, sternite VIII, ventral view. 4, pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view. 5, subgenital plate, ventral view. 6, connective and styles, dorsal view. 7, style, lateral view. 8, aedeagus, lateral view. 9, aedeagus, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457643/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) slightly wider than high. Frontogenal suture extending upwards, beyond antennal ledge, to anterior margin of crown. Antennal ledge, in frontal view, oblique downward in relation to frons; extending inwardly beyond frontogenal suture. Frons (
<figureCitation box="[899,968,724,749]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1931,1954]" captionTargetBox="[168,1408,290,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,280,1905]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Polana (Angusana) pilosa sp. nov., male holotype. 1, head, frontal view. 2, forewing. 3, sternite VIII, ventral view. 4, pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view. 5, subgenital plate, ventral view. 6, connective and styles, dorsal view. 7, style, lateral view. 8, aedeagus, lateral view. 9, aedeagus, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457643/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) slightly swollen; dorsal third concave; lateral margin separated from lateral margin of eye by distance shorter than maximum width of clypeus. Epistomal suture indistinct. Clypeus (
<figureCitation box="[456,522,796,821]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1931,1954]" captionTargetBox="[168,1408,290,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,280,1905]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Polana (Angusana) pilosa sp. nov., male holotype. 1, head, frontal view. 2, forewing. 3, sternite VIII, ventral view. 4, pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view. 5, subgenital plate, ventral view. 6, connective and styles, dorsal view. 7, style, lateral view. 8, aedeagus, lateral view. 9, aedeagus, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457643/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) higher than wide; expanded apically; in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1150,1234,796,821]" captionStart="FIGURES 40–47" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1936,1959]" captionTargetBox="[166,1425,270,1812]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,243,1868]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 40–47. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively. 40 and 41, Polana (A.) pilosa sp. nov., male holotype. 42 and 43, P. (A.) exornata (Fowler, 1903), male allotype. 44 and 45, P. (D.) maculosa sp. nov., male holotype. 46 and 47, P. (D.) danesa DeLong &amp; Freytag, 1972, male holotype. Scale bar = 2.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457651/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Fig. 41</figureCitation>
), slightly swollen medially.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,327,2017]" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">
Pronotum, in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[520,609,868,893]" captionStart="FIGURES 40–47" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1936,1959]" captionTargetBox="[166,1425,270,1812]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,243,1868]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 40–47. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively. 40 and 41, Polana (A.) pilosa sp. nov., male holotype. 42 and 43, P. (A.) exornata (Fowler, 1903), male allotype. 44 and 45, P. (D.) maculosa sp. nov., male holotype. 46 and 47, P. (D.) danesa DeLong &amp; Freytag, 1972, male holotype. Scale bar = 2.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457651/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
), with lateral margins convergent anteriorly; posterior margin slightly excavated; disk transversely striated; in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[753,836,903,928]" captionStart="FIGURES 40–47" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1936,1959]" captionTargetBox="[166,1425,270,1812]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,243,1868]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 40–47. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively. 40 and 41, Polana (A.) pilosa sp. nov., male holotype. 42 and 43, P. (A.) exornata (Fowler, 1903), male allotype. 44 and 45, P. (D.) maculosa sp. nov., male holotype. 46 and 47, P. (D.) danesa DeLong &amp; Freytag, 1972, male holotype. Scale bar = 2.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457651/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Fig. 41</figureCitation>
), strongly declivous anteriorly. Mesonotum (
<figureCitation box="[1346,1428,903,928]" captionStart="FIGURES 40–47" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1936,1959]" captionTargetBox="[166,1425,270,1812]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,243,1868]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 40–47. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively. 40 and 41, Polana (A.) pilosa sp. nov., male holotype. 42 and 43, P. (A.) exornata (Fowler, 1903), male allotype. 44 and 45, P. (D.) maculosa sp. nov., male holotype. 46 and 47, P. (D.) danesa DeLong &amp; Freytag, 1972, male holotype. Scale bar = 2.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457651/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Fig. 41</figureCitation>
) with scutellum slightly swollen. Forewing (
<figureCitation box="[635,702,940,965]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1931,1954]" captionTargetBox="[168,1408,290,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,280,1905]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Polana (Angusana) pilosa sp. nov., male holotype. 1, head, frontal view. 2, forewing. 3, sternite VIII, ventral view. 4, pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view. 5, subgenital plate, ventral view. 6, connective and styles, dorsal view. 7, style, lateral view. 8, aedeagus, lateral view. 9, aedeagus, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457643/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) subhyaline; venation distinct, not reticulated; membrane without punctures; apex rounded; appendix well developed, broad, extending only to second apical cell. Forefemur with AD, AM, and PD rows reduced and poorly defined, except for apical setae AD1, AM1, and PD1, respectively; AV row formed by two or three large setae, spaced apart and restricted to basal half, and large apical seta, AV1, posterior to IC row; latter formed by slightly arched comb of fine setae beginning at apical half of femur and extending to AM1; PV row formed by four to five setae spaced apart and occupying entire femur, proximal setae distinctly smaller than others. Hind leg with femoral setal formula 2:2:1; tibial AD row with long spiniform setae with prominent bases and with two or more intercalary microsetae distributed along distal half; first tarsomere with two parallel rows of setae on ventral surface; pecten with three platellae medially, flanked by longer tapered lateral setae; apex of second tarsomere with two apical platellae flanked by longer tapered lateral setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,327,2017]" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1308,1333]" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Coloration.</emphasis>
Venter pale yellow and dorsum mostly dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[947,1082,1308,1333]" captionStart="FIGURES 40–47" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1936,1959]" captionTargetBox="[166,1425,270,1812]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,243,1868]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 40–47. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively. 40 and 41, Polana (A.) pilosa sp. nov., male holotype. 42 and 43, P. (A.) exornata (Fowler, 1903), male allotype. 44 and 45, P. (D.) maculosa sp. nov., male holotype. 46 and 47, P. (D.) danesa DeLong &amp; Freytag, 1972, male holotype. Scale bar = 2.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457651/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Figs 40, 41</figureCitation>
). Crown (
<figureCitation box="[1198,1283,1308,1333]" captionStart="FIGURES 40–47" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1936,1959]" captionTargetBox="[166,1425,270,1812]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,243,1868]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 40–47. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively. 40 and 41, Polana (A.) pilosa sp. nov., male holotype. 42 and 43, P. (A.) exornata (Fowler, 1903), male allotype. 44 and 45, P. (D.) maculosa sp. nov., male holotype. 46 and 47, P. (D.) danesa DeLong &amp; Freytag, 1972, male holotype. Scale bar = 2.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457651/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
) yellow with brown area between ocelli and dark brown band extending from each ocellus to inner margin of adjacent compound eye. Face (
<figureCitation box="[396,460,1380,1405]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1931,1954]" captionTargetBox="[168,1408,290,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,280,1905]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Polana (Angusana) pilosa sp. nov., male holotype. 1, head, frontal view. 2, forewing. 3, sternite VIII, ventral view. 4, pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view. 5, subgenital plate, ventral view. 6, connective and styles, dorsal view. 7, style, lateral view. 8, aedeagus, lateral view. 9, aedeagus, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457643/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) yellow without distinct maculae. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[975,1056,1380,1405]" captionStart="FIGURES 40–47" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1936,1959]" captionTargetBox="[166,1425,270,1812]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,243,1868]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 40–47. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively. 40 and 41, Polana (A.) pilosa sp. nov., male holotype. 42 and 43, P. (A.) exornata (Fowler, 1903), male allotype. 44 and 45, P. (D.) maculosa sp. nov., male holotype. 46 and 47, P. (D.) danesa DeLong &amp; Freytag, 1972, male holotype. Scale bar = 2.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457651/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
) with pair of dark brown maculae near anterior margin; pair of irregular yellow stripes extending from humeral angles to median region of anterior margin; portion anterad of stripes pale yellow, portion posterad of stripes dark brown; weak yellowish median longitudinal stripe at anterior two-thirds. Mesonotum (
<figureCitation box="[805,894,1488,1513]" captionStart="FIGURES 40–47" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1936,1959]" captionTargetBox="[166,1425,270,1812]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,243,1868]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 40–47. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively. 40 and 41, Polana (A.) pilosa sp. nov., male holotype. 42 and 43, P. (A.) exornata (Fowler, 1903), male allotype. 44 and 45, P. (D.) maculosa sp. nov., male holotype. 46 and 47, P. (D.) danesa DeLong &amp; Freytag, 1972, male holotype. Scale bar = 2.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457651/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
) with anterior half brown and posterior half brownish-yellow; basolateral angles and medioanterior region dark brown; with four small yellow markings, two near basolateral angles and two adjacent to scutellar suture. Forewing (
<figureCitation box="[945,1013,1560,1585]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1931,1954]" captionTargetBox="[168,1408,290,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,280,1905]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Polana (Angusana) pilosa sp. nov., male holotype. 1, head, frontal view. 2, forewing. 3, sternite VIII, ventral view. 4, pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view. 5, subgenital plate, ventral view. 6, connective and styles, dorsal view. 7, style, lateral view. 8, aedeagus, lateral view. 9, aedeagus, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457643/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) mostly dark brown; clavus with four small yellow markings, first basal and adjacent to claval sulcus, second between veins 1A and 2A near base, third and fourth between veins 1A and 2A close to anal margin; corium with costal region with two colorless hyaline areas, one at basal third and another at apical third; one pale yellow macula at base. Legs (
<figureCitation box="[1200,1283,1668,1693]" captionStart="FIGURES 40–47" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1936,1959]" captionTargetBox="[166,1425,270,1812]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,243,1868]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 40–47. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively. 40 and 41, Polana (A.) pilosa sp. nov., male holotype. 42 and 43, P. (A.) exornata (Fowler, 1903), male allotype. 44 and 45, P. (D.) maculosa sp. nov., male holotype. 46 and 47, P. (D.) danesa DeLong &amp; Freytag, 1972, male holotype. Scale bar = 2.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457651/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Fig. 41</figureCitation>
) yellow with proximal and distal portions of tibia dark brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,327,2017]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,151,789]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="145" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,399,1740,1765]" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Male terminalia.</emphasis>
Sternite VIII (
<figureCitation box="[565,632,1740,1765]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1931,1954]" captionTargetBox="[168,1408,290,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,280,1905]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Polana (Angusana) pilosa sp. nov., male holotype. 1, head, frontal view. 2, forewing. 3, sternite VIII, ventral view. 4, pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view. 5, subgenital plate, ventral view. 6, connective and styles, dorsal view. 7, style, lateral view. 8, aedeagus, lateral view. 9, aedeagus, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457643/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) longer than wide, median length approximately 1.3 times greater than maximum width; lateral margins slightly converging towards apex; posterior margin truncated. Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[1319,1386,1776,1801]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1931,1954]" captionTargetBox="[168,1408,290,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,280,1905]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Polana (Angusana) pilosa sp. nov., male holotype. 1, head, frontal view. 2, forewing. 3, sternite VIII, ventral view. 4, pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view. 5, subgenital plate, ventral view. 6, connective and styles, dorsal view. 7, style, lateral view. 8, aedeagus, lateral view. 9, aedeagus, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457643/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) 1.8 times longer than maximum height; dorsal margin approximately straight, without inner process; ventrocaudal margin broadly rounded; apex rounded; macrosetae numerous and distributed throughout dorsal region of apical half. Subgenital plate, in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[575,643,1884,1909]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1931,1954]" captionTargetBox="[168,1408,290,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,280,1905]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Polana (Angusana) pilosa sp. nov., male holotype. 1, head, frontal view. 2, forewing. 3, sternite VIII, ventral view. 4, pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view. 5, subgenital plate, ventral view. 6, connective and styles, dorsal view. 7, style, lateral view. 8, aedeagus, lateral view. 9, aedeagus, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457643/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
), not exceeding pygofer apex; in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[1168,1234,1884,1909]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1931,1954]" captionTargetBox="[168,1408,290,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,280,1905]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Polana (Angusana) pilosa sp. nov., male holotype. 1, head, frontal view. 2, forewing. 3, sternite VIII, ventral view. 4, pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view. 5, subgenital plate, ventral view. 6, connective and styles, dorsal view. 7, style, lateral view. 8, aedeagus, lateral view. 9, aedeagus, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457643/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
), 4.7 times longer than maximum width; lateral margins approximately parallel, except at basal third where outer margin is laterally expanded; apex rounded; ventral surface with numerous filiform elongate setae distributed adjacent to whole external margin. Connective (
<figureCitation box="[483,550,1992,2017]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1931,1954]" captionTargetBox="[168,1408,290,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,280,1905]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Polana (Angusana) pilosa sp. nov., male holotype. 1, head, frontal view. 2, forewing. 3, sternite VIII, ventral view. 4, pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view. 5, subgenital plate, ventral view. 6, connective and styles, dorsal view. 7, style, lateral view. 8, aedeagus, lateral view. 9, aedeagus, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457643/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
) Y-shaped; stem slightly shorter than arms; total length about one-third of style length. Style, in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[501,574,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1931,1954]" captionTargetBox="[168,1408,290,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,280,1905]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Polana (Angusana) pilosa sp. nov., male holotype. 1, head, frontal view. 2, forewing. 3, sternite VIII, ventral view. 4, pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view. 5, subgenital plate, ventral view. 6, connective and styles, dorsal view. 7, style, lateral view. 8, aedeagus, lateral view. 9, aedeagus, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457643/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
), with outer lobe developed and produced; in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1277,1350,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1931,1954]" captionTargetBox="[168,1408,290,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,280,1905]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Polana (Angusana) pilosa sp. nov., male holotype. 1, head, frontal view. 2, forewing. 3, sternite VIII, ventral view. 4, pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view. 5, subgenital plate, ventral view. 6, connective and styles, dorsal view. 7, style, lateral view. 8, aedeagus, lateral view. 9, aedeagus, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457643/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
), blade slightly curved dorsally; ventral margin slightly serrated at median portion; apex rounded and contoured by several tiny denticles. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[438,536,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1931,1954]" captionTargetBox="[168,1408,290,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,280,1905]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Polana (Angusana) pilosa sp. nov., male holotype. 1, head, frontal view. 2, forewing. 3, sternite VIII, ventral view. 4, pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view. 5, subgenital plate, ventral view. 6, connective and styles, dorsal view. 7, style, lateral view. 8, aedeagus, lateral view. 9, aedeagus, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457643/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Figs 8, 9</figureCitation>
) with preatrium very short; dorsal apodeme developed, bearing pair of processes directed posteriorly and bent dorsally at right angle, apexes of processes expanded and bilobate, ventral lobe longer, thin, and acute in comparison with dorsal lobe; shaft compressed laterally, broad at basal half, apical half narrowing progressively towards apex; with pair of slight flanges at median third of shaft; apex with pair of short and thin lateral processes, directed dorsally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,789]" box="[199,400,404,429]" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Female unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="145" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,789]" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,439,464]" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name of the new species alludes to the filiform setae that cover the subgenital plates (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1931,1954]" captionTargetBox="[168,1408,290,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,280,1905]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Polana (Angusana) pilosa sp. nov., male holotype. 1, head, frontal view. 2, forewing. 3, sternite VIII, ventral view. 4, pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view. 5, subgenital plate, ventral view. 6, connective and styles, dorsal view. 7, style, lateral view. 8, aedeagus, lateral view. 9, aedeagus, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457643/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Figs 4, 5</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
