<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="145" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,789]" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,620,645]" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Gonçalves &amp; Takiya &amp; Mejdalani, 2018" authorityName="Gonçalves &amp; Takiya &amp; Mejdalani" authorityYear="2018" box="[323,618,620,644]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Polana" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilosa" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Angusana">
<emphasis box="[323,404,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Polana</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[421,533,620,643]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Angusana</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[550,618,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">pilosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[628,718,620,645]" pageId="2" pageNumber="145" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[628,718,620,645]" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fowler" baseAuthorityYear="1903" box="[869,1048,620,644]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Gypona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exornata" subGenus="Angusana">
<emphasis box="[869,890,621,644]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">P.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[907,932,620,643]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">A.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[948,1048,621,644]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">exornata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in appearance and color (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 40–47" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1936,1959]" captionTargetBox="[166,1425,270,1812]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,243,1868]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 40–47. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively. 40 and 41, Polana (A.) pilosa sp. nov., male holotype. 42 and 43, P. (A.) exornata (Fowler, 1903), male allotype. 44 and 45, P. (D.) maculosa sp. nov., male holotype. 46 and 47, P. (D.) danesa DeLong &amp; Freytag, 1972, male holotype. Scale bar = 2.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457651/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Figs 42, 43</figureCitation>
). However, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fowler" baseAuthorityYear="1903" box="[320,450,656,680]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Gypona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exornata">
<emphasis box="[320,334,657,680]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[350,450,657,680]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">exornata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the new species in having the style with apex acute and without denticles and the aedeagus with shaft compressed dorsoventrally and with two pairs of subapical processes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
